com.avaya.ic.sdk

Interface Session


  • public interface Session
    A Session is created when an agent logs in successfully to IC. The Session represents the IC session for that logged in agent (end-user with allocated Channels to process work). The Session contains references to the enabled Channels, Worklist, User and AddressBook for the agent. The Session also provides data pertinent to that session.

      • enterAuxwork

        void enterAuxwork(ReasonCode reasonCode)
        Makes the logged in agent move to an auxilliary work state. In that work state, the logged in agent does not receive new work. If the agent is already in Auxwork, You may call this API to change reasonCode. OperationSucceeded or OperationFailed event will be fired upon Completion of the transition, depending on the outcome. When the reasonCode is changed, the server will fire LastAuxReasonCodeChanged event for the changed reasoncode. See also: LastAuxReasonCode property on Session, LastAuxReasonCodeChanged event.
        Parameters:
        reasonCode - The code for the reason that the logged in agent wants to enter the auxilliary work state.

      • enterAuxwork

        void enterAuxwork()
        Makes the logged in agent move to an auxilliary work state. In that work state, the logged in agent does not receive new work.

        IC Properties that affect this API:
        Agent/Desktop/AuxNotAvailableReasonCode, Agent/Desktop/SystemAuxgroup, Agent/Desktop/SystemAuxgroupTenant

        Returns:

      • beginSupervising

        void beginSupervising()

        Triggers to start the supervisor session and request all online agents, in this supervisor's workgroup, to send a list of all workitems the agent is handling. The supevisor will inturn start receiving WorkList.WorkItemAdded or WorkList.WorkItemRemoved event, depending upon the current state of workitem been handled by agent. The supervisor can then start monitoring the workitems.

        Only agent with supervisor role can perform this operation. Session.OperationFailed event will be raised, if agent performing this operation is not a supervisor.

      • endSupervising

        void endSupervising()

        Triggers to stop the supervisor session and request to remove all the supervised workitems from its worklist.

        Only agent with supervisor role can perform this operation. Session.OperationFailed event will be raised, if agent performing this operation is not a supervisor.

      • requestWorkitems

        void requestWorkitems(java.lang.String agentId)
        The supervisor can request for workitems for a particular agent, to which he/she wants to monitor.
        Parameters:
        agentId - The id of the agent to which workitem request will be send.
